added.title: Little Elvis
added.description: The Titans team up with Shazam in order to defeat the evil Mr. Mind.

added.title: Booty Eggs
added.description: Not wanting to be creeped out on Easter the Titans dispatch the Easter Bunny and take matters into their own hands.

added.title: TV Knight 4
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon go camping but instead of fun outdoor activities they'd rather watch TV.

added.title: Lil' Dimples
added.description: Thinking it's a way to reconnect with her father, Raven enters a beauty pageant.

added.title: The Teen Titans Go Easter Holiday Classic
added.description: The Easter Bunny is missing, and it's up to the Titans to find him before Easter is ruined.

added.title: The Spinoffs
added.description: Wishing to get rid of Gumball once and for all, his nemesis Rob offers up a variety of reality, action and comedy shows featuring characters other than Gumball. Unfortunately for Rob, each one is worse than the last.

added.title: The Transformation
added.description: Penny's family is unhappy that she's decided to come out of her shell literally. And Penny wants her family to come out of their shells...also literally. They are at an impasse so who do they turn to in their time of trouble? Gumball of course! Needless to say he is way outside of his comfort zone.

added.title: The Understanding
added.description: Gumball and Darwin find themselves in serious trouble when they agree to everything the new kid in school says. The truth is they can't understand a word that he says. Peter Pepperoni has been home schooled and developed a very odd way of speaking. Due to a series of misunderstandings Gumball and Darwin end up on the run from the law.

added.title: The Ad
added.description: To make ends meet, the Wattersons are forced to rent out their house. However, with nowhere else to stay they decide to secretly remain at the house. When they accidentally surprise their guests, an elderly pair of fainting goats, they faint...unsurprisingly.  The Wattersons fear the worst and attempt to cover up this "accident".

added.title: The Ghouls
added.description: It's Halloween in Elmore. As the kids go trick or treating we see what everyone in town is up to. The ghosts and ghouls are finding it increasingly difficult to scare children, and are only scaring part-time. Can Gumball and Darwin help them get their scare back?

added.title: Fan or Foe
added.description: When Elder Con comes to the Creek, Craig, Kelsey and JP each have a con experience they'll never forget.

added.title: New Jersey
added.description: After donning a brand new Jersey, JP is recruited by the Hockey Kids! The only way to get JP back is for Craig and Kelsey to hit the ice!

added.title: The Sunflower
added.description: Our Trio makes a new friend in the Creek, but when her pet befalls a tragic fate, Kelsey believes she knows how to help.

added.title: Craig World
added.description: Craig creates an amusement park in the Creek! But when things start to get stale, he vows to make it bigger and better, no matter what it takes!

added.title: Body Swap
added.description: Fed up with their home experiences, Craig, Kelsey and JP agree to switch bodies!

added.title: Onionless
added.description: Onion needs to leave town so Apple has to survive the weekend alone while taking care of Onion's beloved plant.

added.title: Party Popper
added.description: Apple and Onion's party plans are interrupted by a grumpy guest.

added.title: Face Your Fears
added.description: Apple and Onion must face their fears if they are to save French Fry from their bad advice.

added.title: Apple's Short
added.description: Apple wants to experience love.

added.title: Positive Attitude Theory
added.description: Apple and Onion spend a day in Falafel's shoes and use their positive attitude to prove he shouldn't be so grumpy.

added.title: Video Date
added.description: Panda is an avid e-dater, and when a lovely French woman matches with him and agrees to a video chat date. Panda and his brothers engineer the situation so Panda is able to show the best side of himself on the video chat, even if that side of him is completely exaggerated.

added.title: Pet Shop
added.description: Pet Shop tells the tale of where the Baby Bears once lived, and after a run-in with a video crew shooting a Sarah McLachlan-type animal adoption video, almost seized an opportunity to find a home separated from each other.

added.title: Chloe and Ice Bear
added.description: On a day out with just Ice Bear, Chloe realizes Ice Bear only runs errands for his brothers. Determined to show him a fun day in the city, Chloe promises to help Ice Bear have a good time, even if it means staying  in a museum after it closes.

added.title: Cupcake Job
added.description: When the Bears' beloved laptop breaks, they finally have the need to do something they've never done before: get jobs. Working at a trendy cupcake shop, the Bears find  that the working world is much tougher than they realized.

added.title: Hibernation
added.description: The bears, being an urban bunch, hadn't ever heard of the idea of hibernation until Chloe tells them about it. Grizz, loving the idea of eating a ton and then just sleeping to his heart's content, goes for it with reckless abandon.  But Grizz is so excited for hibernating... that he can't fall asleep.

added.title: The Question
added.description: Steven shows some city slicker gems how the cowboys lived.

added.title: Made of Honor
added.description: Steven has a big surprise for the Crystal Gems.

added.title: Reunited
added.description: Steven brings everyone together for a special reunion.

added.title: Legs from Here to Homeworld
added.description: Steven travels to visit family.

added.title: Familiar
added.description: With many changes going on in his life, Steven tries to find his place in the world.

added.title: Hot to the Touch
added.description: Finn goes on a quest to prove Flame Princess isn't really evil.

added.title: Jake vs. Me-Mow
added.description: Finn and Jake grapple with a tiny feline assassin.

added.title: The New Frontier
added.description: When Jake has a dream that predicts when his last days are, Finn intervenes when the events of the dream start to actually happen.

added.title: Incendium
added.description: Jake sets Finn up with the Flame Princess with fiery results.

added.title: Marceline's Closet
added.description: Finn and Jake spend a nerve-wracking afternoon trapped in Marceline's closet.

added.title: Picking Up Margaret
added.description: Mordecai wants to give Margaret a ride to the airport.

added.title: K.I.L.I.T. Radio
added.description: Muscle Man wants a local radio station to play the song he wrote for Starla.

added.title: Carter and Briggs
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby enter a donut contest to win a cameo on their favorite cop show.

added.title: Skips' Stress
added.description: Skips has to lower his stress before it kills him.

added.title: Cool Cubed
added.description: The guys need to unfreeze Thomas' brain after he chugs a slushy.

added.title: Sun Scream/City of Frownsville
added.description: Sun Scream: The girls get the ultimate sunburn and must try to fight crime despite their UV damage./The City of Frownsville: When the tearful Lou Gubrious sets a crying ray on Townsville, the girls must find a way to stop the tears before the town is flooded.

added.title: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs/Mizzen in Action
added.description: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs: The girls must literally work as one to try and stop Mojo from destroying Townsville./Mizzen in Action: Captain Crack McGraigen and his crew are tossed forward in time where discover the chemical X that marks the spot and it is up to the girls and Professor to send the super-charged pirates back to their own time.

added.title: That's Not My Baby/Simian Says
added.description: That's Not My Baby!: The girls save a baby from a monster attacking Townsville but can't find the mother. Can these three superheroes manage to take care of one little baby?/Simian Says: When the Narrator is mysteriously bound and gagged, Mojo Jojo takes over his job, ordering the girls to steal for him all around Townsville.

added.title: West in Pieces
added.description: It's the old west and Mojo the Kid has robbed the first bank ever and forced the sheriff out of town and it is up to the Steamypuff Girls to save the day at a high-noon showdown.

added.title: Aspirations
added.description: The Gangreen Gang is actually committing brilliant crimes. But behind every great gang, there has to be a great woman.

added.title: Lights Out!
added.description: When Bliss brings a new tech product to town, it's more powerful than imagined.

added.title: Bucketboy!
added.description: When the girls tell Barry he's a hero, he takes it too far.

added.title: The Fog
added.description: A new villain arrives in Townsville and gives the old villains an enticing offer.

added.title: The Spoon
added.description: A crash landing sends Townsville over the edge.

added.title: Cat Burglar
added.description: An alarmingly familiar cat burglar terrorizes Townsville.

added.title: Unikitty News!
added.description: You're watching the Unikingdom News Show Super Good Morning Time Program Action Information Show, a variety news program put on (badly) by Unikitty and the gang: Hawkodile does the weather, Puppycorn does sports despite knowing none of the rules, Dr. Fox puts on a fun science-y cooking segment that goes awry, and Richard wants this to stop. Unikitty's got some hard hitting reporting and a big scoop after the break, if the studio survives that long!

added.title: Dinner Apart-y
added.description: Unikitty and Puppycorn are invited to Master Frown and Brock's apartment for a dinner party. But the two roommates are butting heads, and are anything but on the same page. Can Unikitty help Brock and Master Frown get back in harmony before the dinner party is ruined? Will Puppycorn figure out which door is the bathroom?

added.title: R & Arr
added.description: It's Lazy Sunday, and Unikitty and Puppycorn are having such an amazing time hanging out on the couch, they never want to move! Richard insists they have chores to do, but they're unwilling to let Lazy Sunday end. The two go to ridiculous lengths to never leave the comfort of their sofa, rowing it across the castle and like a ship and conscripting their friends to abandon their chores and join Lazy Sunday… no matter how dangerous and impossible it might become!

added.title: License to Punch
added.description: Hawkodile's caught by the Action Police for bodyguarding without an Action License. He's can't protect the kingdom or do anything rad until he does, but the test at the DMV (The Department of Mayhem and Violence) is for nerds! Forced to retire his gloves, Hawkodile struggles to live a life without punching, so Unikitty vows to help her friend contain his urge to be action-y and study for the test. But there's more to the test than meets the eye.

added.title: Buggin' Out
added.description: When Unikitty and the gang discover a gross bug in the castle, they desperately want it gone for good, but Unikitty refuses to allow them to squish it, no matter how icky or dangerous looking it is. What sort of web is Unikitty weaving for her friends?

added.title: Merry Moochmas
added.description: It's wintertime in Aberdale and Clarence is convinced his winter wish for snow in Arizona will come true! However, his classmate Belson along with his grumpy cousin Gary Mooch are a little tougher to convince.

added.title: Pizza Hero
added.description: It's the end of the school year, and as is tradition at Aberdale Elementary, Papa Marianio is slated to dish out his famous pizza along with a spectacle of song and dance. As the kids wait in excitement, they share memories about times with Papa.

added.title: Sumo Goes West
added.description: Clarence learns his best friend Sumo may transfer to another school! It's up to Clarence to protest, petition and rally to convince everyone to let Sumo stay - or face losing his closest school pal!

added.title: Valentimes
added.description: When Clarence notices his teacher Ms. Baker is the only one in class left without a Valentine this year, he decides to enlist the help of Sumo to set her up with Sumo's teacher, Mr. Mozer! Will sparks fly or will the boy's naive view of romance backfire?

added.title: Clarence for President
added.description: It's school election time at Aberdale Elementary, and Jeff is once again determined to become Class President. However like previous years, he's unsuccessful in connecting with other kid. That is until he sees a shoe-in puppet President, the lovable Clarence!

added.title: RV Olympics
added.description: Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus compete in the RV Olympics.

added.title: Uncle Melvins
added.description: Legendary rock band, the Melvins, team up with Uncle Grandpa to help a young girl who wants to win her school's talent show.

added.title: Uncle Baseball
added.description: A failing little league team on the brink of giving up gets help from Uncle Grandpa and some Major League Baseball players.

added.title: Costume Crisis
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes improvements to a kid's Halloween costume.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Runs for President
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve run against one another in the RV presidential race.
